<Review ID>9098189
<Product Name>Apple 160 GB iPod classic (Black)
<Title>Who ate all the pies?
<Date>Tue Dec 11 00:00:00 CST 2007
<Content>I have to say I was a little concerned when I ordered the 160gb Ipod Classic.  Reading the reviews the classic seemed to be suffering a variety of problems ranging from from being slower than a speeding snail to the battery draining faster than George Bush can start a war. Fortunately my Ipod has shown none of these tendencies.  I have noticed some slowness sometimes in accessing the menus but it is not consistent.  I have now loaded most of my 400 odd compact discs and have used less than a quarter of it's capacity.  Where I have noticed some differences from the 5th generation 30gb Ipod I  replaced is in the sound quality. I use V-Moda earbuds with both Ipods and the 5th generation had much more punch and more control than the classic. I would suspect that the power configuration has been altered in the classic to provide the 40 hour battery life which has robbed the unit of some of its control of the speakers at the sharp end of the earbuds.  I cannot actually comment on whether this Ipod delivers the claimed 40 hour battery life (audio) as I have not had the battery fail on me. What I can say is that I took the Ipod to England and used it fairly heavily over 18 hours and according the pictogram used less than 25% of the charge.  Of course we have the new Coverflow system" which looks very nice but is fatally flawed. I tend to listen to a variety of music, most of which is older and a little more obscure. Often Itunes cannot find the album artwork for the albums I have loaded which leaves big gaps in the parade of album covers. How bad is this? I recently loaded 5 Ac-Dc albums and Itunes couldn't find covers for any of them! I cannot believe that "Back in Black" could be considered "obscure." So while I can understand not finding a cover for "Ashton/Lord - The First of the Big Bands," not finding "The Eagles - Hotel California" is reprehensible!  No doubt Apple will offer an excuse about licensing etc. but if they are going to use "Coverflow" as a feature then most would expect them to have their "ducks in a row."  Apart from the difference in sound quality (hey it's an Mp3 player.... right?) and the flaws in the "Coverflow system" the Ipod Classic has generally been what I expected, except for one thing.....   Apple boasted that this unit was thinner so I have to ask; than what?  The Ipod Classic is at least twice as thick as my 5th generation which has resulted in me having to discard my Belkin car charger and F.M. transmitter. The Ipod will no longer fit in the cradle, it is just too fat! At first I thought; "No problem, I'll just replace it" except..... I can't.  A quick call to my local Apple store quickly established that there is no immediate replacement for the Belkin (or any other manufacture.) Nice planning Apple!  Overall, despite these niggles I am very happy with the 160gb Ipod Classic. It does what I need it to do.   
